    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Species of tree native to western Australia, distinctive among bloodwoods in having very large buds and fruit, "honky nuts." The species is confused with the related red-flowering gum (Corymbia ficifolia), but differs in being much taller (50 meters, 160 feet); hybridization between the two makes identification difficult. Formerly classified in genus Eucalyptus, until the mid-1990s. </Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
